               <head>Tarikh-i Mahmudshahi</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Tārīkh-i Maḥmūd Shāhī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85064911 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008115302" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3841-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>Anonymously-written official regnal chronicle for the reign of <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="viaf_50479847" ref="http://lccn.loc.gov/n78027870" role="pat">Sultan Mahmud Begarah</persName> written in florid prose, extending from 896/1490-1 to 916/1511, intended as a supplement to the anonymously-written Maʾās̲ir-i Maḥmūdshāhī 
                        </p>
                        <p>According to Storey (p. 726), this volume apparently contains only the first two maqālahs described in the preface, with accounts for Mahmud Shah and his contemporaries </p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 60v): completed Sunday, 12 Shavvāl 1299/27 August 1882, in the city of farkhandah bunyād Ḥaydar'ābād (Deccan), within the office of the Garīntar (Guarantor) for the Navvāb Niẓām al-Mulk Āṣafjāh, by ʿAbd al-Razzāq. Checked by ʿAbd al-Raḥmān, 13 Shavvāl 1299/28 August 1882 </p>
                        <p>IOL stamp 15 Aug. 1913 </p>
                        <p>Bound with IO Islamic 3842 </p>
                        <p>Bound in original covers, signed Yūsuf ʿAlī the ṣaḥḥāf </p>
                        <p>Transcribed in clear and neat shikastah āmīz, with large naskh for quotations, with flecked mica </p>
                        <p>Notes of ownership at beginning </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
